Chinese Stocks in the U.S.: AsiaInfo-Linkage, Cnooc, JinkoSolar

-- B y   Y e   X i e
-- 
2011-09-19T21:22:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-19/chinese-stocks-in-the-u-s-asiainfo-linkage-cnooc-jinkosolar.html
The Bank of  New York  Mellon  China 
ADR Index, which tracks American depositary receipts, fell 1.6
percent to 386.31. The New York Stock Exchange China Index
retreated 1.5 percent to 235. The Shanghai Composite Index
declined 1.8 percent to 2,437.80, the lowest level since July
2010.  The following companies were among the most active Chinese
shares in New York trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
prices are as of the close of trading at 4 p.m. New York time.  AsiaInfo-Linkage Inc. (ASIA)   lost 17 percent, the most
since July 2010, to $9.25. The telecommunications software
company was downgraded to ’’neutral’’ from ’’positive’’ by James Friedman, an equity analyst at Susquehanna International Group
in New York. The 12-month target price is $11 per share.  China Unicom Ltd. (CHU US) rose 0.7 percent to $22.07. The
nation’s second-largest mobile-phone carrier said it added 2.4
million mobile subscribers in August, the biggest increase since
April.  Cnooc Ltd. (CEO)  , China’s largest offshore energy
producer, tumbled 3.9 percent to $169.98, the lowest level since
August 2010. PetroChina Co. (PTR US), the nation’s biggest oil
producer, fell 2.5 percent to $122.41. Crude oil dropped 2.6
percent to $85.70 a barrel on the  New York Mercantile Exchange .  JinkoSolar Holding Co. (JKS US) sank 28.1 percent to $6.50,
the lowest level since it started trading in May 2010. The solar
equipment producer said in a statement that it suspended
operations at a factory in Haining, Zhejiang province until an
environmental investigation can be completed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ye Xie in New York at 
